All Official Questions

Explore a comprehensive repository comprising every official GMAT question ever released, meticulously compiled from Official Guides, Verbal and Quantitative Reviews, paper tests, and GMAT Advanced editions up to OG 2022. These curated links grant access to the entirety of official GMAT questions, all meticulously categorized and presented for the convenience of GMAT aspirants.

GMATClub, with explicit permission from GMAC, hosts this invaluable resource within its GMAT question bank, ensuring legality and authenticity.

This collection categorizes official GMAT questions by type, difficulty, subtlety, and topic, affording test-takers a structured approach to honing their skills. Each link seamlessly navigates to GMATClub's platform, facilitating easy access to these crucial resources.

Maximize your study efficiency by adhering to a strategic approach: commence with questions of lower difficulty and progress methodically towards more challenging ones. Engage with topics systematically rather than haphazardly selecting questions. Additionally, leverage the expertise of GMATClub's community, where seasoned professionals provide comprehensive solutions to aid yourÂ understanding.

All Official Critical Reasoning Questions

Here's how to navigate the table effectively:

To focus on Easy Assumption Critical Reasoning questions, simply access the Critical Reasoning table and select 'Easy' under the Assumption row. This will display a comprehensive list of all easy CR Assumption questions officially released by GMAC.

For a broader practice session encompassing all Assumption questions, regardless of difficulty, click on the Assumption link in the first column. This will present you with a compiled list of all CR Assumption questions, spanning easy, medium, and hard levels.

If you prefer a varied set of easy CR questions, click on ALL CR Easy.

To engage with a diverse array of all CR questions, regardless of type or difficulty, select All Critical Reasoning.
